Twenty eight year old Sean Hendricks has been sentenced to life imprisonment for the rape of his then girlfriend. Hendricks was also given 20 years in jail for attempted murder that occurred in September 2020 in Alexandria in the Eastern Cape. This comes after an appearance at the Makhanda High court. The High Court heard evidence of the traumatic experience endured by the 18-year-old victim in 2020. The victim was severely injured, with several stab wounds. It was established that she was also raped. Police spokesperson Thembinkosi Kinana says Hendricks could not escape the sentencing due to the overwhelming evidence against him. SA rape stats In November last year, Police Minister Bheki Cele said it is a disgrace and deeply disturbing that almost 10 000 people were brutalised by crimeÂ in a space of three months. Crime statistics for the 2021 second quarter period from the 1st July to the 30th September showed an increase of 4.7% in sexual offence cases. Video | Cele releases crime statistics:  Reporting rape Victims of sexual assault are urged to report the abuse within 72 hours in order to receive medication that prevents the infection of HIV/AIDS. Some victims, under current lockdown, might find it hard to report abuse. Below are some steps that one can take after a sexual assault:  